    "Name": "Burke (HPPC)",
    "Details": "<b>Name: <color=#85DBF6>Burke Defense Tank (HPPC)</color>\nArmor: <color=#85DBF6>Ferro-Fibrous</color>\tTechnology: <color=#85DBF6>Inner Sphere</color>\nMovement: <color=#85DBF6>2/3 (Tracked)</color>\tEngine: <color=#85DBF6>150 Fusion</color></b>\n\nThe Burke, created as a static defense vehicle for the SLDF, was noteworthy for its devastating long-range firepower. It was highly prized by garrison forces, and ComStar secretly maintained a number of them in operational condition within the Inner Sphere.\n\nThis Jihad-era variant, seen in Word of Blake and ComStar forces, replaces the three PPCs with two Heavy PPCs and the LRM-10 with a four-tube Streak SRM launcher. Two additional tons of armor and an Improved C3 Network Computer System give the tank crew unprecedented targeting ability.",
